RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 78. Claiming Purse 19000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since June 9 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $9,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it wil l be run on the maintrack at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 14 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KLAYTON'S KANDY set a pressured pace early on the inside, shook clear by the five eighths marker, then drew off leaving the turn and was kept to left handed crop to remain clear. FILLMORE EAST was settled early two wide, advanced four wide by the quarter pole, then finished well to be clearly second best. GIRL'S ON FIRE was well placed early on the inside, made a three wide move on the turn but flattened out, bested rest. SASSY MARTINI was reserved on the inside, shifted off the inside on the turn, came three wide into the lane and had no rally. BRUMMAGEM tracked the pace three wide, made a two wide bid on the turn but weakened. BONITA LASSIE pressed the pace two wide and weakened. KENTUCKY PRIDE was reserved three wide and failed to menace. CAR LADY was void of early speed and was not a threat. BELLS ON HER TOES was not a factor.
